Fast and Lightweight Bioinformatics PubMed Miner

A simple Streamlit web app that fetches the latest research articles from PubMed based on your input keywords. Useful for bioinformatics and computational biology students who want quick access to relevant research literature.

Features

Real-time search of articles from PubMed

Displays article title, authors, publication date, and abstract

Lightweight and easy to run (no heavy AI models)

Requirements

Python 3.7 or higher

Required Python libraries: streamlit, requests

Installation and Deployment

Clone or download this repository
git clone https://github.com/Asimahafeez/LiteratureMiner/new/main
cd LiteratureMiner

Install required packages
pip install -r requirements.txt

Run the app
streamlit run app.py

The app will open automatically in your browser or provide a URL to open manually.

Usage

Enter your research keyword or topic in the input box (for example, bioinformatics)

Select the number of articles to fetch

Click the Fetch Articles button

View summaries and details of the fetched articles

Notes

Internet connection is required as the app fetches live data from PubMed API

The app is optimized for basic search and lightweight use
